# Conventional Commits format:
# <type>(<scope>): <description>
#
# Types:
#   feat     (new feature)
#   fix      (bug fix)
#   docs     (documentation)
#   style    (formatting, missing semi-colons)
#   refactor (code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature)
#   perf     (performance improvement)
#   test     (adding missing tests)
#   chore    (updating tasks, release bumps, no production code change)
#
# Examples:
#   feat(ui): redesign landing page with editorial dark mode
#   fix(service): prevent crash on null SMS body
#   chore(release): bump to v1.1.1
#   docs(readme): update installation instructions
#
# Keep the description concise (<72 chars), imperative mood, no period.